  "experiments_summary": "The paper presents a comprehensive evaluation framework integrating DFT simulations with ML metrics for assessing generative materials models. Two experimental approaches were employed: (1) A perturbative approach applying controlled distortions to known materials from Materials Project (MP, 87k structures) and OQMD (221k structures) datasets at three scales (small, medium, large) across three modes (atomic positions, lattice parameters, combined); (2) A generative model approach training and evaluating three diffusion models (CDVAE, GemsDiff, DiffCSP) on preprocessed MP and OQMD datasets (structures up to 64 atoms, formation energy <0.1 eV/atom). The framework automates DFT calculations using VASP with PAW pseudopotentials and PBE-GGA functional, performing both static energy calculations (for SUN metric on 1024 structures) and geometry optimization/relaxation (for RMSD on 64 structures). Evaluation metrics span three categories: simulation-based (RMSD measuring atomic displacement after relaxation, SUN assessing stability/uniqueness/novelty via convex hull analysis with 0.1 eV/atom threshold), property-based (EMD on density and formation energy, validity checking minimum interatomic distances >0.5Å), and latent-based (precision/recall using CrystalNN fingerprints, Fréchet distance). Additional preprocessing includes symmetry analysis via SpacegroupAnalyzer, duplicate removal using StructureMatcher, filtering of unreactive elements and F-block elements, and band gap estimation using the Δ-Sol method. Phase diagrams were constructed from reference structures to evaluate energy above hull for stability assessment."
